# LinkedIn Internships – Complete Guide 2026

Guide for Indian students and recent graduates to find internships using LinkedIn in 2026 — from school students to final-year / postgraduate level.

**Who this guide is for:**
- 11th & 12th school students exploring early opportunities
- 1st & 2nd year college students (limited/no experience)
- 3rd & 4th year undergraduates looking for paid or skill-building roles
- Final-year students, postgraduates, gap-year candidates targeting higher stipend, remote, or reputed companies

LinkedIn is widely used in India for internships in **tech, marketing, finance, startups, and MNCs**.  
As of early March 2026: **5,000–6,000+ active internship/entry-level postings** in India (including remote/hybrid options).  
Popular companies: Microsoft, Google India, Unacademy, Deutsche Bank, PwC, startups, etc.

**LinkedIn vs Internshala**  
LinkedIn → networking, referrals, profile strength, hidden opportunities, better brand-name roles  
Internshala → high-volume applications with custom questions  
Most students use **both**.

