- Tier-2/3 city students (use remote filter + network)

No strict CGPA cut-off for most roles.

## 3. Step-by-Step Process

### 3.1 Profile Optimization (Most Important)

1. Go to https://www.linkedin.com (use personal email)
2. Fill key sections:
   - **Headline**: "2nd Year B.Tech CSE | Seeking Software Internships | Python | Java | Projects"
   - **About**: 3–5 lines (education + skills + goal)
   - **Education**: College, branch, year, relevant subjects
   - **Skills**: 10–15 relevant (Python, SQL, Canva, Excel, Communication…)
   - **Experience/Projects**: College projects, events, volunteering (link GitHub/Behance)
   - **Photo**: Clear professional headshot
   - **Custom URL**: linkedin.com/in/yourname-lastname
3. Turn ON **#OpenToWork** banner → select "Internships", add "Remote" / "India"

**Beginner About example:**
"1st year B.Com student from Maharashtra. Interested in digital marketing & content. Self-taught Canva + basic analytics. Managed local event promotions. Looking for remote internships to learn practically."

### 3.2 Finding Internships

1. Go to **Jobs** tab → search "Internship" or "Data Analytics Internship India"
2. Filters:
   - Experience level: Internship / Entry Level
   - Location: Remote / India / your city
   - Date posted: Past month
   - Easy Apply: quick applications
3. Follow target companies (their posts show in feed)
4. Set job alerts: "Internship + your field + Remote"
5. Follow hashtags: #InternshipsInIndia #SummerInternship2026 #Hiring

### 3.3 Applying & Networking

Two ways:
- **Easy Apply**: upload ATS-friendly PDF resume
- **Direct outreach** (best for beginners): message recruiters/alumni

**Connection request example:**
"Hi [Name], I'm a 2nd year CSE student interested in software roles at [Company]. Would love any advice on openings!"

**Tips:**
- Research profile/post before messaging
- Keep messages short (3–5 lines)
- Weekly goal: 10–20 applications + 10–15 connections
- Track everything in a spreadsheet

Beginners: like/comment on posts → then connect/message alumni/seniors/HR

### 3.4 Interviews & Follow-up

Common format: Google Meet / Teams / phone  
Common questions:
- Tell me about yourself
- Why this role/company?
- Explain a project
- Strengths & weaknesses
- Availability

Follow up: thank-you message within 24 hours

## 4. Strategies by Level

**Beginner (Low/No Experience)**
- Target startups, NGOs, content/marketing roles
- Post learnings/projects 1–2×/week
- Use "Remote + Entry Level + Internship"
- Add free certificates (Coursera, YouTube)

**Intermediate**
- Highlight projects / fest roles
- Aim ₹8,000–₹20,000 stipend
- Ask connections for referrals

**Advanced / Final Year**
- Apply early for summer 2026
- Target MNCs / good startups (₹15,000+ or PPO chance)
- Use alumni network heavily

## 5. Application Tracker (Spreadsheet Columns)

- Date applied/contacted
- Company & Role
- Contact name
- Method (Easy Apply / Message)
- Status
- Follow-up date
- Notes

## 6. Why You Get Low Responses (Fix These)

- Weak/incomplete profile
- Generic copy-paste messages
- No prior engagement (like/comment first)
- Only using Easy Apply, no networking
- No follow-ups

**Scam alert**: Never pay any fees for internships.

## 7. Timing & Location Tips

- Early 2026: summer roles already opening
- Peak season: Feb–May
- From smaller towns (e.g. Shirpur, Maharashtra): use "Remote" filter + connect with Pune/Mumbai professionals

## 8. LinkedIn vs Internshala Summary

- LinkedIn → networking, referrals, premium brands
- Internshala → mass applications, student-focused
→ Use both!

